Definition: Born in the U.S. (50 US States)
RESIDENT: State and county of occurrence and residence are the same.
INTRASTATE NONRESIDENT: State of occurrence and residence are the same but county is different.
INTERSTATE NONRESIDENT: State of occurrence and residence are different but both are one of the 50 US states or District of Columbia.
FOREIGN RESIDENT: The state of residence is not one of the 50 US states or District of Columbia.
RESIDENT: State and county of occurrence and residence residence are the same.  (Unique to Guam, all US residents are considered residents of Guam and thus are assigned 1.)
INTRATERRITORY NONRESIDENT: Territory of occurrence and residence are the same but county is different.
INTERTERRITORY RESIDENT: Territory of occurrence and residence are different but both are US Territories.
FOREIGN RESIDENT: The residence is not a US Territory.
